# Network Infrastructure Documentation: VLAN, DNS, and NAT

## IX. Virtual Local Area Network (VLAN) Implementation

VLANs segment a single physical switch into multiple logical networks to improve security and reduce broadcast traffic.

### 1. Conceptual Overview

A **VLAN** allows an administrator to group devices by function or department rather than physical location.

* 
**Security**: Sensitive departments like Finance can be isolated from the rest of the network.


* 
**Performance**: By reducing the size of broadcast domains, VLANs prevent network congestion caused by broadcast storms.



### 2. Switch Configuration (CLI)

The following steps create the VLAN database and assign physical ports to the logical segments.

```ios
! Accessing Global Configuration Mode
enable
configure terminal

! Step A: Define VLAN IDs and Names
vlan 10
 name IT
exit

vlan 20
 name Finance
exit

! Step B: Assign Ports to VLANs (Access Mode)
interface range fa0/1 - 5
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 10
exit

interface range fa0/6 - 10
 switchport mode access
 switchport access vlan 20
exit

! Step C: Configure Trunk Links (Multi-switch communication)
interface g0/1
 switchport mode trunk

```

