## X. Domain Name System (DNS) Services

DNS translates human-readable domain names into the numerical IP addresses used by routers.

### 1. Conceptual Overview

DNS is essentially the "phonebook" of the network. When a user enters a URL, the PC queries the DNS server to find the destination IP.

* 
**A Record**: Maps a domain name (e.g., `www.abc.com`) to an IPv4 address.


* 
**Automation**: DHCP pools should be configured to provide the DNS server IP to clients automatically.



### 2. DNS Integration and Server Setup

To implement DNS, the server must have a **Static IP**, and the routers must point clients toward that IP.

**Router DHCP Update:**

```ios
ip dhcp pool ABC
 dns-server 192.168.30.10  ! Directs clients to the DNS Server

```

